Data Analytics Portfolio Projects
This repository contains two industry-standard Power BI business intelligence projects designed to showcase end-to-end data modeling, ETL pipelines, and interactive executive reporting.

Project 1: E-Commerce Sales & Inventory Dashboard
📊 Objective
To design and implement a dynamic E-Commerce & Inventory Management tracking system. This project mirrors modern supply chain retail environments by connecting operational warehouse stock metrics directly with customer transaction lifecycles.

🏗️ Architecture & Data Modeling
Data Preparation: Structured a two-tier relational schema using flat sheets created in Microsoft Excel.

Product_Inventory Table: Tracks core product attributes (Product_ID, Product_Name, Brand, Stock_Quantity, Unit_Cost).

Online_Orders Table: Records sales executions (Order_ID, Product_ID, Payment_Method, Order_Amount, Shipping_Status).

Data Model: Established an optimized 1-to-Many (1→∗) relationship in Power BI's Model View via the Product_ID key, enabling strict cross-filtering continuity across discrete tables.

📈 Dashboard Key Features
Global Performance Matrix: Top-level Card visuals parsing absolute transactional variables (e.g., Total Revenue Generated via Sum of Order_Amount).

Inventory Distribution Analysis: A Clustered Column Chart (Brand vs. Stock_Quantity) mapping immediate warehousing liabilities across manufacturing brands.

Transactional Architecture Split: A specialized Donut chart mapping transaction volumes (Count of Order_ID) over user payment channels (COD, Credit Card, UPI).

Logistics Bottleneck Funnel: A strategic breakdown mapping financial capital (Order_Amount) tightly against logistical fulfillment states (Delivered, Pending, Cancelled).

Interactive Slicers: Integrated structural page filters for Brand and Shipping_Status to evaluate custom operational conditions instantaneously.

Project 2: Amazon Global Sales Performance Analytics Platform
📊 Objective
A comprehensive deep-dive enterprise dashboard built to analyze long-term financial health and operational indicators for a large-scale global marketplace ecosystem, as modeled in Screenshot 2026-06-02 213454.jpg.

🗃️ Data & KPI Insights
The architecture processes multi-year sales ledgers stretching across historical timeline trends (2012 – 2015) to distill core health metrics into high-impact visual components:

Total Revenue: Tracked at $1.28M in gross sales volume.

Net Profits: Aggregated at $194.46K in corporate profit metrics.

Units Moved: Aggregated product tracking at 3K absolute distributed units.

Logistics Failures: Hard metrics pinpointing 500 specific returned items.

📈 Visual Mechanics & Features
Temporal Trend Matrix: A dedicated time-series pie chart highlighting granular structural changes in annual turnover (e.g., 2014 contributing $327.8K vs. 2012 contributing $316.3K).

Segment-Wise Breakdown: A categorical split visualization tracing consumption behavior trends down across business pillars: Corporate (37.16%), Consumer (32.19%), and Home Office (30.65%).

Geographic Sales Split: A performance-oriented column visualization separating transactional volume across global theater segments (Europe, LATAM, USCA, Asia Pacific, Africa).

Customer Tier Analytics: Dual horizontal bar charts tracking localized customer performance metrics, filtering top-performing assets by overall purchasing margins alongside the Top 5 Profit-Generating Customers (e.g., Christopher, Daniel Griggs).

UI/UX Formatting: Built upon a professional dark-themed layout using custom container blocks and integrated card-style wrappers to preserve dashboard layout hierarchy.

🛠️ Tech Stack & Concepts Demonstrated
Tools: Power BI Desktop, Microsoft Excel, Power Query Editor.

Data Modeling: Star Schema Design, 1-to-Many Relational Integrity.

BI Engineering: Cross-filtering optimization, Implicit Aggregations (SUM, COUNT), Slicer synchronization, Interface design rules (contrast, visual flow, information chunking).
